Requirement Understanding

I reviewed the FRD document and understood the business requirements.

The available data contains information related to:
Customers | Policies | Claims | Agents | Transactions | Locations

The management team wants to analyze premium collections, claims performance, customer distribution, agent performance and product performance.

=================================================================================================================

Task 1: Business Understanding

After reviewing the FRD, I identified the main business entities.

Customer | Policy | Claim | Agent | Transaction | Location

These entities are required to support all reporting and analytical requirements mentioned in the FRD.

====================================================================================

Task 2: Relationship Analysis

After identifying the entities, I analyzed the relationships between them based on the business rules.

1. One customer can have multiple policies.
2. One policy belongs to one customer.
3. One policy can generate multiple claims.
4. One agent can manage multiple policies.
5. One location can have multiple customers.
6. One transaction belongs to one policy.

These relationships were used while designing the dimensional model.

===========================================================================================

Task 3: Data Modelling Approach

Based on the business requirements, I implemented a dimensional data model.

Dimension Tables:

DIM_CUSTOMER | DIM_AGENT | DIM_POLICY | DIM_LOCATION | DIM_DATE 

Fact Tables :

FACT_PREMIUM | FACT_CLAIMS

This model supports reporting, analytics and dashboard development.

=========================================================================

Task 4: Source Data Preparation

The source data was provided in Excel format.

The Excel file was converted into Parquet format and uploaded into AWS S3.

Data Flow : Excel → Parquet → AWS S3 → Snowflake

===========================================================================================

